The Senate Justice and Legal Affairs Committee has until 2pm Thursday to table the public participation report to the House.Speaker Ekwee Ethuro gave the team led by Amos Wako two hours to put together the report and present it for discussion.The committee set to present the electoral law amendments report was said to be in a meeting at the time the speaker issued the orders.In a gazette notice on Wednesday, Ethuro said Election Laws (Amendment) Bill, 2016 will be the only business of the day.Earlier this week, he directed the committee to invite public input on amendments to the contentious law.The senators met on December 28 to consider controversial changes adopted by the National Assembly on December 21.The changes have been opposed by Cord leaders and members of the opposition, key among issues raised being the manual versus electronic voter registration system.Jubilee said the manual voting system should be in place just in case technology fails.Read: Raila gives Uhuru nine-day ultimatum on election laws, says demos a last resortChanges to the laws will force a mediation between the Senate and National Assembly.Read: Speaker Ethuro orders police to withdraw from parliament ahead of election laws debateAlso read: Election laws: Anxiety as Senate decide